    "faqs": [
      {
        "question": "Is an MRA/MRV scan painful?  ",
        "answer": "No injections feel like a routine blood test; the scan is painless.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": " How long does an MRA/MRV scan usually take?",
        "answer": "An MRA/MRV scan typically takes between 30 to 90 minutes. The exact duration depends on the specific body part being scanned, the number of imaging sequences required for a comprehensive assessment, and whether contrast is administered.  "
      },
      {
        "question": "How soon are results available?",
        "answer": "Most patients receive reports the same evening; emergency cases within 30 minutes.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": " What is the main difference between a regular MRI and an MRA/MRV?",
        "answer": " While both regular MRI and MRA/MRV use the same fundamental MRI technology (magnets and radio waves), MRA/MRV uses specialized software and imaging sequences optimized to visualize blood vessels (arteries for MRA, veins for MRV). A regular MRI focuses on imaging general organs, soft tissues, bones, and other structures.  "
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I drive after contrast?",
        "answer": "Yes, unless you take sedation. In that case, bring a friend to drive home.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "How much does an MRA/MRV scan cost at Cadabams Diagnostics?  ",
        "answer": " The cost of an **MRI Angiogram/Venogram (MRA/MRV)** scan varies. Factors influencing the price include the specific body part imaged, whether a contrast agent is used, and the complexity of the study. For detailed pricing information, contact Cadabams Diagnostics directly."
      }
    ],
