    },
    "markdown": "## MRA/MRV (Magnetic resonance angiogram/venogram) Overview\n\nNeed a closer look at the blood vessels inside your head or neck? Cadabams Diagnostics offers a \\*\\*fast, painless MRI Angiogram/Venogram (MRA/MRV)\\*\\* — no surgery, no radiation, and results ready within hours. Scan time is only 20–40 minutes, and you can book online in under two minutes.\n\n## Risks & Limitations of MRA/MRV\n\n### Contrast Dye Cautions\n- Rare allergy (<1 %)\n- Requires good kidney function (eGFR ≥30)\n### Magnetic Field Restrictions\n- Pacemakers, cochlear implants, and certain aneurysm clips may be unsafe\n### Claustrophobia Solutions\n- 70 cm wide-bore scanner\n- Mirror glasses, music, or mild sedation on request\n\n## List of Parameters Considered During MRA/MRV\n\n| Parameter | What We Measure |\n|-----------|-----------------|\n| Vessel lumen diameter | Width of the artery/vein |\n| Flow velocity | Speed of blood movement |\n| Stenosis % | How much vessel is narrowed |\n| Thrombus presence | Blood clots |\n\n## When to Take Test\n\n- \\*\\*Detecting aneurysms\\*\\* – ballooning artery walls before they rupture\n- \\*\\*Evaluating venous sinus thrombosis\\*\\* – clots in brain veins that mimic migraine\n- \\*\\*Monitoring vasculitis\\*\\* – inflamed vessels causing daily headaches\n\n## Benefits of Taking the Test\n\n- \\*\\*Zero radiation\\*\\* – safe for children and repeated follow-ups\n- \\*\\*High-resolution head vessels\\*\\* – see 1 mm abnormalities\n- \\*\\*Single exam covers MRA MRV head\\*\\* – arteries and veins in one appointment\n\n## Illnesses Diagnosed with MRA/MRV\n\n- Carotid stenosis\n- Dural sinus thrombosis\n- Arteriovenous malformations (AVMs)\n\n## Preparing for MRA/MRV\n\n### Fasting Guidelines\n- Nothing by mouth 2 h before if contrast is planned\n### Metal Implant Screening\n- Fill safety questionnaire; bring implant card\n### Best Time to Schedule Exam\n- Morning slots = shorter fast and quicker report\n---\n## Pre-Requisites\n- Recent eGFR blood report (if contrast needed)\n- Previous imaging CDs for comparison\n- Documented allergy history\n---\n## Best Time to Take the Test\n- \\*\\*Morning slots\\*\\* – lower waiting time and full radiologist support\n- \\*\\*Emergency stroke protocol\\*\\* – 24×7 availability with neurologist on call\n---\n## Eligibility\n- Adults and children above 5 years (younger kids need sedation)\n- Pregnancy: MRA without contrast is safe; consult your doctor\n- Weight limit: 150 kg (330 lb) table capacity\n---\n## Procedure for Taking an MRI Angiogram/Venogram\n1. \\*\\*Check-in & IV line\\*\\* – 10 min\n2. \\*\\*Scanning steps\\*\\* – lie still for 20–40 min; expect loud knocking sounds\n3. \\*\\*Post-contrast observation\\*\\* – 15 min to watch for rare reactions\n---\n## Caution Before Taking the Test\n- Contrast allergy? Pre-medication provided\n- Renal function below threshold? We switch to non-contrast sequences\n- Severe claustrophobia? Oral sedation available—bring an escort"
